column5: Exciting progress by the Zoox team! First time in history a robotaxi has driven autonomously on open public roads with passengers. Congrats to the team and excited for more milestones to come!

Tragic news out of Turkey and the surrounding region. We’re activating Amazon’s logistics and delivery network to quickly get donated relief items such as blankets, tents, heaters, food, diapers, baby food & medicine to those in need. https://t.co/aQjfJ5vcsF
Well done, Darrell!

Nearly half of adults take 2 or more medications daily & many find it hard to afford them. Am excited about launching RxPass to help. For just $5 a month, Prime members can fill all their eligible medications (shipping included, no hidden fees or markups). https://t.co/Xfo4qCV3zw

Thinking today about Dr. King's legacy and the continued work required to build a more just and inclusive world. Progress has been made, but still a long way to go. Something we’ll all need to be relentless about for many years to come.

Excited to be expanding Buy With Prime, letting more merchants offer fast, free delivery on their websites to Prime customers. Early tests show shopper conversion increases an avg of 25% when using Buy With Prime. Compelling for merchants & Prime customers.https://t.co/8t8lzgSO9E

Proud of our Thursday Night Football team for making history this season with 4 of most watched telecasts of 2022, 1st time ever a streamer has had programs on this list. Even more proud of the quality of the broadcast this team produced every week. And, just year one…

Love seeing notes like this from customers who see our @Rivian EV delivery vans out and about. Excited to share that we just hit the 10 millionth package delivered since our first Rivian EV hit the road in July. #ClimatePledge

Loved meeting our special group of Amazon Prime members we invited to last night’s Thursday Night Football game. Thank you to the millions of fans who watch @NFLonPrime every week... https://t.co/n2guUDKg4F

Am excited to see HBO Max back on @PrimeVideo. It’s great for Prime customers, and we continue to work hard to make Amazon an easy one stop shop for customers to enjoy the best and widest selection of premium content available. https://t.co/x5X3fXjZ1J

Throughout history, brave men and women have answered the call of duty when they’ve been needed most. Thank you to our over 50k Amazon military veterans and spouses, and all who have served. Incredibly grateful for your service. https://t.co/VELFBFKMwr

Excited about meaningfully enhancing our music benefit for Prime members. Starting today, Prime members can now shuffle play more than 100 million songs (up from 2 million) on @AmazonMusic, and listen to many top podcasts ad-free. https://t.co/b65bmXnFR7

Loved visiting our Boston Robotics center, where our team is working hard on inventing robotics that help keep our employees safe and improve delivery for our customers. Excited about what the team is working on. https://t.co/4MkICPYPE7
Proud of how Amazon continues to help in times of urgent need…thx to the collective Amazonians who are making this happen! https://t.co/HILRmZZSmf

Nearly impossible to imagine what it would be like to flee your country & have to start over… to help millions of Ukrainians who now face this & those still in the country, we are offering them free cloud skills training & AWS Certification vouchers. https://t.co/GOvsm08MQK
Excited to be kicking off the holiday season early this year for our Prime members. Prime Early Access sale starts today... https://t.co/K0NwKshw1G

Enjoyed being in Dartford today visiting one of our 30 Amazon fulfillment centers here in the UK (+80 across Europe). Very impressed by the site leadership & thankful for the chance to meet so many of our team members throughout the tour. Thank you for taking care of customers! https://t.co/oltzwllE0B

Amazon is committing €1 billion to further electrify & decarbonize our transportation network across Europe. Will help us shift further away from traditional fossil fuels & scale innovation. Very important we continue to invest in a sustainable future. https://t.co/onnmgR8lI7

Great Amazon Devices event today... here’s a look at the new products we announced and how they further our vision for ambient intelligence—technology that’s there for customers when they need it & disappears when they don’t. https://t.co/PJtOM0Hstm
Thinking of everyone in Florida right now... we have activated our teams to prepare relief items to send to Florida when Hurricane Ian makes landfall. https://t.co/c5aTSLJHeh https://t.co/u3QA3pUdZG

Hurricane Fiona has left many in Puerto Rico without electricity, shelter & clean water. Amazon has activated our Disaster Relief Hub in Atlanta where hundreds of thousands of much-needed items are being packed for shipping directly to the island to help. https://t.co/ue2l1vWAjL https://t.co/NmBXib3Xjp

Our first renewable energy project in South America & first solar farms in India & Poland… part of 71 new renewable energy projects. Last yr, Amazon powered 85% of our business w/ renewable energy… w/ today’s additions, closer to our goal of 100% by 2025.https://t.co/kHyWo8aeJz

Tonight, we kick off a new era of @NFL Thursday Night Football only on @PrimeVideo. Huge team effort getting to this moment, and we can’t wait to deliver a great experience for Prime members this season + the next 10. Giddy up! https://t.co/CBKUcMSbiu
Amazing story & selfless act by Amazon delivery driver Kevin Rivera… grateful to hear everyone is safe and well.
Sad day for so many around the world…On behalf of Amazon, sharing our deepest sympathies for the Royal Family and all of those in mourning.
Congrats team & thanks to all the @PrimeVideo members who tuned in!

Amazon continues to invest in range of new technologies to get to net-zero carbon by 2040. Excited about latest step...in 2025, we'll start purchasing ~11K tons of green hydrogen/year -- enough annual power for 30,000 forklifts or 800 heavy-duty trucks. https://t.co/oWwWT0DHk9

Really enjoyed being with the talented cast and creators at #TheRingsofPower premiere. So much care and passion has gone into this project…looking forward to our Prime customers all over the world being able to see. Just a few weeks away from release on @PrimeVideo. https://t.co/iLiv6WrwNW

Fortunate to know Tom Alberg for the last 25 yrs. His professional & civic accomplishments were many. But, what impressed me most was his character—humble, high integrity, missionary, cared about his community—as good a guy as they come. Learned a lot from Tom. Will miss him. https://t.co/KRLh1TwWAv

This show truly has been a labor of love for the @PrimeVideo team, with each and every detail obsessed about to bring these characters to life... can’t believe we’re just one month away until #TheRingsOfPower debuts.

Really enjoyed spending time with Al Michaels, @KirkHerbstreit, and the rest of the talented production, on-air, and Amazon TNF team yesterday as part of the @NFLonPrime production kickoff this weekend. Think you’re going to like watching this group and what they have planned. https://t.co/GsCAcFjHOn

Excited about first electric @Rivian vans hitting the roads today to deliver for Amazon customers. Love thoughtful design around safety, driver comfort & low emissions to help us reach our @ClimatePledge. Thx @RJScaringe for the tour and partnership! https://t.co/zeJJHnboct https://t.co/avom4Fdcum

Think customers really enjoyed Prime Day ‘22—our biggest ever w/ 300M+ items sold & $1.7B+ saved by Prime members. Prime Day is a massive team endeavor—thank you, thank you, thank you to our teams, 3P sellers & delivery partners for your incredible work. https://t.co/3zcxU70YSY
Getting closer to the launch of The Lord of the Rings #TheRingsOfPower, and can’t wait to share with you all. Here’s a little taste… https://t.co/9GH1Tkry3Y
20 countries…millions of deals…Happy Prime Day! https://t.co/wAPCzRd4Bu https://t.co/ALNq7LlSoO

Juneteenth is not just a lesson from the past…it’s both a time to reflect on this country's painful history of slavery and racism (which we must face & learn from) and a chance to recommit as a nation to confront the inequalities that exist today.
The date for Prime Day 2022 just announced…gonna be a lot of great deals for customers. Giddy up!

Deeply sad about the shootings in Texas yesterday and Buffalo 11 days ago. My heart breaks for those families. This endless cycle is maddening…terrible pain and suffering. I can only hope that we come together as a country to find a way to stop this kind of tragic violence.

Great progress being made in India...Amazon teams are working hard to make the lives of customers better every day. Excited for everyone joining the #AmazonSmbhav summit - lots of important discussions on how to empower entrepreneurs + SMBs. https://t.co/mxFi2UOQ0W
If not already watching, recommend you add this to your list. Less than a month until season three begins!

Incredible teachers make a real difference in the lives of their students…

Congrats to this year’s #AmazonFutureEngineer Teacher of the Year $30K prize recipients. Thx for helping students see that anyone can pursue a career in computer science.
https://t.co/VY3rA7VbtC
Prime getting even better for members… :) https://t.co/ePn5zJEERx
Another important step toward our mission of running Amazon’s global operations on 100% renewable energy by 2025 – 5 years ahead of our initial goal.
https://t.co/Kxq57wYBZG
https://t.co/XZs0mUutGY

Congrats to Zoey and the rest of this year's 250 #AmazonFutureEngineer $40K college scholarship recipients. Just the beginning of big things for all of you… excited for your Amazon internships to begin. https://t.co/6YyHBHyGHe https://t.co/pC5a47rq0L
Still plenty more to do, but proud of our incredible teammates who make this a special place to work…

Excited for Project Kuiper to partner w/ @Arianespace, @ulalaunch & @blueorigin to deploy 3K+ broadband satellites in the coming years. Scale of this agreement will help us bring fast, affordable broadband to customers in unserved & underserved communities.https://t.co/ApkkFTCLm5
.@ZachPerson here playing between periods at #Kraken game. Imo, best up and coming rock artist around. His self-titled record is fantastic. https://t.co/pohAFFTKGL

Rain outside not dampening Amazon #MARS2022… some of brightest minds in machine learning, automation, robotics and space. Feel lucky to be surrounded by so many brilliant and accomplished people working on next generation of disruptive inventions. https://t.co/2zjwxrF5WV
Am so sad and bummed to hear about Taylor Hawkins. Unbelievable musician, force of nature in Foo Fighters, really likable guy, and my thoughts and heart go out to his family (and the band).
Very excited to have you and Al join the team, Kirk! Looking forward to the start of #TNFonPrime!

First shipments of critical supplies just arrived at a fulfillment center in Slovakia we’ve converted into a humanitarian aid hub. This will help charities get needed items to Ukrainian families faster. More help coming soon through our logistics network. https://t.co/NPEsI2kzJc https://t.co/AJLPgUOltV
(2/2) Our latest partnership ($124M) will build 1K+ homes next to public transit. https://t.co/PXLsGritxj

As we continue to increase our focus on the communities in which we have a substantial presence, we’re excited to invest further in affordable housing. To date, we've committed more than $1.2B to create/preserve 8,000+ homes and help ~18K people. (1/2)

Important milestone for the #ClimatePledge - 300+ companies have now joined Amazon in committing to reach net-zero carbon emissions by 2040. Innovation and collaboration are key to solving big global challenges…encouraging to have these companies on board.https://t.co/IcvDZsvVIZ

Appreciative of our incredible women leaders and builders. Our teams are stronger and products are better when they include diverse perspectives and experiences. We’re committed to supporting women and their careers here at Amazon. #InternationalWomensDay #IWD2022

Good luck to Garfield HS Girls Basketball team in WA State Finals tonight. What a year they’ve had! Same for Boys team, which finished 4th in State tournament + lost only 1 game all year. Impressive to watch hard work/commitment all year by these athletes. https://t.co/bcxrLV5nf1 https://t.co/3UjzJWxgPT

(2/2) We’re supporting humanitarian relief NGOs on the ground with cash donations from Amazon and our employees, logistics to get supplies to people needing them, and cyber security assistance to companies and governments.
The situation in Ukraine is deeply concerning, and gets more so each day. Amazon stands with the people of Ukraine, and will continue to help. (1/2)

Enjoyed visiting w/ @lazowska & @greggottesman's class last night. So impressed w/ @UW and the clever composition of comp sci, design, and MBA students in this class who collaborate to conceive and build real products. I would have loved to take this class when I was in school. https://t.co/BcmVoKwvhY

Pretty cool to see...over weekend Lost Ark became 2nd highest played game in Steam history (1.325M concurrent players). On the heels of New World success a few mos ago, team has found two games in a row that seem to be resonating with gamers. https://t.co/ZmhtXKE7CW
The first official trailer of The Lord of the Rings 'The Rings of Power' coming to @PrimeVideo Sept. 2. #SBLVI #LOTRROP #LOTRonPrime https://t.co/q0u57pLpLB
Hey #LOTRonPrime fans…be ready during 3rd quarter of #SBLVI. We have something during one of the commercial breaks for you.

Have loved football since my dad took me to my very first @Giants game when I was 3...very excited to have Thursday Night Football come exclusively to @NFLonPrime starting September 15! https://t.co/apP6JUYIU2
For people excited to see what Middle-earth will look like, here’s a first look at our new @LOTRonPrime series. https://t.co/djLqaNqmZW
Very cool story about one of our Amazon Delivery Service Partners...in less than 2 years, Jaren has grown his team to almost 80 employees. https://t.co/yQuCxuhfCy
Looking forward to the Super Bowl on Sunday…here’s a first look at one of our new commercials for it. https://t.co/LH9WeDUFRR

Proud of the fact that Amazon has been voted one of the most admired companies in the world for the sixth year straight (#2). We have a lot to keep working on, and committed to getting better every day, but feel lucky to work with the folks that I do. https://t.co/KqfGAGgCI7

Our employees are now eligible for fully-funded college tuition from Amazon after just 3 mos (we had Career Choice for yrs, but had a 1 yr requirement). Accessible, affordable education is so important & such a door opener. Hoping this makes it easier for even more employees.

Very excited to share this with customers…we're opening Amazon Style, our first-ever physical store for apparel. It will be located in L.A. and use machine learning and a unique store design to create a customized experience for each shopper. https://t.co/rKsQAVPYqW
A lot of people are excited for the upcoming @LOTRonPrime series (including me!). Today, we officially share its name...Can’t wait for the premiere September 2!

“Commit yourself to the noble struggle for equal rights. You will make a greater person of yourself, a greater nation of your country, and a finer world to live in.” -MLK
 
Reflecting on how Dr. King’s ideals of democracy, justice, hope, and love can help us grow as a society.
Excited to collaborate with @Stellantis to re-invent the driving experience. This partnership will make driving safer, smarter, and more personalized for millions of people. https://t.co/vcs8bkER7b

Alexa has made life easier for customers on Earth...excited to explore what voice & AI can do for astronauts in space. Great partnership with @LockheedMartin & @Cisco for @NASA’s upcoming #Artemis mission! https://t.co/tUfXSJngcH

(2/2) As this situation continues to evolve, I want our Edwardsville community to know we are working closely with local officials & first responders to support them. My deepest sympathies are with the Amazon community and all impacted.
We've been closely monitoring the terrible situation in Edwardsville, and are heartbroken over the loss of our team members. Our thoughts are with their families at this difficult time. (1/2)

Addressing the affordable housing crisis in underrepresented communities starts with removing barriers. Amazon’s new program provides Black, Hispanic & Native American real estate developers w/ training, mentorship & capital to kick-start their projects. https://t.co/GbqbVyHeUp
We've been fortunate to have Grab build their business on top of #AWS for many years now. Am super impressed with @AnthonyPY_Tan and the Grab team and excited for them as they go public today.
Excited for #AWS customers and AWS team as they gather for the 10th annual #reInvent...lot in store for customers and will be fun for the community to be together again.

Loved this photo one of our Amazon Air team members took recently in Lakeland, Florida. Sending a big thank you to our teams, partners, and sellers heading into the holidays. Appreciative of all you do for customers… https://t.co/X7rRiJ3Zhy
Good update on last year’s pledge to expand access to free cloud skills training.

This country would not be what it is today without the incredible bravery and sacrifices of our military community. Thank you to all veterans - those at Amazon and beyond - for your service. https://t.co/te21VYvhBp

We've announced today that Amazon will be a founding member of the First Movers Coalition, leading to more sustainable technologies across freight, ocean & air transport. Energized to see this collaboration as we push toward net-zero carbon. #COP26 https://t.co/rZVHIc8KwE

Excited to share that Project Kuiper will launch two prototype satellites next fall on ABL Space Systems’ new RS1 rocket…an important step toward making fast, affordable broadband a reality for unserved & underserved communities. https://t.co/SQSw4zkkj1
Pre-game at the arena...new era of NHL hockey in Seattle about to begin. Go Kraken! #seakraken https://t.co/QAWvwLCpdh

Proud of how we’re helping people with Amazon’s Returnship program. Life happens…we want to make it easier for people who’ve taken a break in their careers to come back to work. https://t.co/xAeU9NoXgA
Can’t wait!

So many cool parts of this building: ice rink made from rainwater, powered by 100% renewable electricity, tickets that double as transit passes, etc. Excited to officially open the doors of @ClimateArena tomorrow. Congrats to @OakViewGroup & all involved! https://t.co/dzVeBEK2Gk

Cool video of @zoox all-electric, fully autonomous robotaxi. Amazon joined forces with Zoox last year and it’s been exciting to see their technology evolve. They’ve just started testing their L3 vehicles in Seattle…the rainy weather should be great training for the fleet and AI.

Tonight's beginning for @SeattleKraken is long time in making...takes a village to bring new things to life, and this was no different. Pretty amazing team on + off ice...tonight is a new starting line for the Kraken-- giddy up!

Josh’s pioneering work on Alexa’s Show & Tell accessibility feature, which helps customers who are blind or visually impaired identify household items, is just one of the ways he’s made people’s lives better on a daily basis. Congrats on being named a MacArthur Fellow, Josh!

Congrats to the Amazon Devices team on the array of amazing products announced today! And, thx for sneak peek on Astro…looking forward to customers getting a chance to benefit from a totally new kind of home robot. https://t.co/4b0MsbGcpI
Really excited about today’s New World launch. More than 1 million people have been playing in Beta tests, and today, the rest of the world gets to fight for survival.
Excited about this…
Many folks have had situations that have gone awry and where you have to improvise...few have done it gracefully as what I'm watching tonight with Dave Matthews... https://t.co/LvuCt0I86W

Thinking of communities in Louisiana following #HurricaneIda. Our Disaster Relief team sent trucks in & is working w/ @SaveTheChildren…getting 140,000+ Amazon-donated aid supplies like water, hygiene products & diapers to families today. More is on the way. https://t.co/4MjWAemEY1

Excited to welcome job seekers around the world to Career Day in a few weeks, our big recruiting and training event. With over 55k jobs available globally, look forward to helping people learn more about these roles and launch their next chapters. https://t.co/RcsMCPha9e

Today is the 15 year anniversary of EC2. Offering developers compute for $0.10/hr was pretty radical back in 2006, it's now become the norm and backbone for so many new and existing businesses. And, the #AWS team isn't close to being done innovating on EC2. Lots more to come.
RIP Rod Gilbert...an amazing player, a NY Ranger through and through, a class act, and an important figure in my childhood

Seattle, we now have players on the @SeattleKraken :-). Very impressive work from GM @RonFrancis10 and his amazing Scouting and Analytics teams to assemble this initial Kraken squad…only 3 mos before we release the Kraken at @ClimateArena.
Congrats, @JSalke and the @AmazonStudios and @PrimeVideo teams on today’s Emmy nominations!
Proud that Amazon continues to support our U.S. veterans and military spouses...we employ over 40K, and making a pledge to hire 100K more in the next few years. https://t.co/8s6RXRpcLG

This is pretty cool, imo…introducing the #AWS Bug Bust Challenge, the world’s first global competition to fix a million bugs so #developers can improve code quality, eliminate bugs, and boost app performance https://t.co/k3IB1dCJDr

Excited to continue to innovate with Amazon's $2B+ Housing Equity Fund with a new $300 million investment to provide thousands of affordable homes near public transportation. Big step towards empowering communities. https://t.co/JeuTi3yBsp

Black-owned businesses are too often locked out of traditional ways of accessing capital, mentorship, and resources. We're committed to changing that. Proud of our Black Employee Network and Seller teams for making this accelerator a reality. https://t.co/Cw9iqvbq2E

Hard not to love @brandicarlile if you're a music fan, but also if you ever get a chance to talk with her. Smart, thoughtful, authentic. Can see it in her memoir Broken Horses, and in the interview she did with me today. Thx for stopping by Amazon, Brandi! https://t.co/F4QqUiwxa1

Ever thought about how many scenarios come into play when matching 32 teams across 17 games during an 18-week period… all while optimizing for fairness, travel, & venue availability? Customers like @NFL don't have to w/ #AWS #compute https://t.co/emobvio7s0

Congratulations to Samuel, Kelly, and all 100 #AmazonFutureEngineer 2021 scholarship recipients. An education in computer science can unlock so many opportunities, and I can’t wait to see these incredible students at Amazon for their internships. https://t.co/3Pr8VzYXD8 https://t.co/jox5mnueO9

Amazon has joined The Global Task Force led by @USChamber to help source and deliver medical equipment to India. 1000 ventilators are on their way to local hospitals in India with the first 100 arriving today. The challenges in India will take continued focus--more help is on way
Proud of this one...lucky to work with the teammates I do on the customer missions we're aiming to solve... https://t.co/SzTp0cEVCe

Very serious situation in India. Our teams are moving fast to provide support for the latest wave of #COVID19, and using our global and India-wide operations network to transport medical supplies. This is just one step, more help is on the way.

Excited about teaming up with @DISHNews for telecom 1st...DISH will leverage #AWS infrastructure to build 1st cloud-based 5G network from ground-up (leveraging AWS for RAN and Core, too). Beginning of shift in how telco networks will be built... 
Link: https://t.co/rpHZ5CJmt9

Thanks to @AmitAgarwal and the Amazon India team for having me. Their investment in small and medium businesses is driving remarkable innovation and economic growth in India, and the new Smbhav Venture Fund will keep that momentum going
Excited to expand our relationship and can’t wait to see all the #5G use cases that Private MEC will enable...
The increasing anti-Asian violence in this country is pretty shocking and deeply concerning. At Amazon & AWS, we stand in solidarity w/ the Pan-Asian community. #StopAsianHate
Like Don, am pretty excited about the new x2gd instances...really substantial compute savings-- driven again by graviton2 chips
Pretty cool to see 12 Oscar nominations for @PrimeVideo, including Sound of Metal for Best Picture. Congrats, team! #OscarNoms https://t.co/moZjeHq3ix
Happy #InternationalWomensDay. I’m fortunate to have been shaped by many smart, courageous, resilient women throughout my life & career at Amazon.

Teeing off @AWScloud’s collaboration w/ the @PGATOUR to change the way golf fans connect – giving them real-time access to virtually every moment on the course & letting *them* determine how they experience the game ⛳ #sports #digitaltransformation https://t.co/RtdpFLWx0m
Congratulations to the @AmazonStudios team on a great night! #GoldenGlobes
@hadip @amazon @jeffawilke Thanks to you & the whole team, Hadi. We're passionate about the mission of helping all students have access to learning CS.

Excited about the release of Amazon Lookout for Vision, a new industrial #machinelearning service that uses #AWS-trained computer vision models to help customers like @GEHealthcare spot defects or anomalies in products & processes https://t.co/NhegQbmaMi
Really cool to be a part of this historic mission to bring the images & sounds of #Mars back to Earth w/ @NASAJPL @NASAPersevere #CountdownToMars #AWS #space https://t.co/9fFJmHeT5y

Enjoyed chatting w/ @CommissionerNHL to announce how @AWScloud will support the @NHL in its digital transformation. Look forward to seeing goal & faceoff probability stats in action in an upcoming @SeattleKraken game :-) #AWS #machinelearning

OK, that was an action-packed week :-)...Grateful for all the people who’ve reached out, to Jeff for (the first) 24 yrs of learning & partnership, and for the opportunity to work with the incredible teams across Amazon. Excited for what the future holds.
